	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117950><span id= >Abrethel</span></a><br><span id=notbold>12 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The epic EFFECT stacks with other haste spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;That does not mean that the haste component does.<br><br>Ex.1)  Chanter casts VQ on a group, and a bard procs epic (or clicks this!)  The VQ has the higher haste - and predominates - however the bard adds the STR and pure ATCK to the group.<br>Ex.2)  Low level shammy hastes group (say, 40% or so... ) Bard procs epic.  The Bard's haste predominates, although the shammy's buff icon remains (and that's good, cause the proc only lasts a few mins).  Note that if the bard procs epic BEFORE, the shammy won't be able to buff the group with the weaker haste.  Need to click off the bard buff.<br><br>Only a couple things are STACKED hastes - and are bard songs (best = Rizlona's) - which will stack with other spell hastes, and will allow you to go over the haste cap.<br><br>for the eleventy-millionth time:<br>Haste = Item + best Spell + overstacked Bard song.<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
